details.title: IELTS Listening - Overview
details.description: Wondering how your IELTS listening test is? Check this video and know the different parts of IELTS listening, the duration of the test and many more details about it.

details.title: IELTS Listening -Myth busted
details.description: Here is an in-depth discussion of the IELTS listening test. Aspects like time-management, answer formats and much more to come. Watch on and find out!

details.title: IELTS Listening- Question Types
details.description: This video will bring you all the types of questions that a candidate will face in the IELTS listening test. Pay close attention to all the different types of questions and let the learning begin.

details.title: IELTS Listening- Common errors
details.description: Putting down a 'Distractor'; as an answer is a common mistake made by students in the IELTS Exam. This video will surely help you resolve a number of common mistakes. Let's take a look at them.

details.title: Form/ Note Completion Question type
details.description: Note completion questions appear frequently on the IELTS Listening exam, so there's a good possibility you'll get one.

details.title: Table Completion Question type
details.description: Table completion is a prevalent type of question in IELTS listening. It could show up in any part of the listening exam. Spend time crafting the headings and predicting the table's lacking material. Take a look and know more about it!

details.title: Summary Completion Question type
details.description: This video discusses the summary completion question of the IELTS listening test. You'll be given a summary of the recording to answer summary completion questions. A recorded monologue on an academic subject, such as a lecture about the Amazon jungle or the Pyramids of Giza, will usually be played. There will be words in the summary that need to be filled in.

details.title: Sentence Completion Question type
details.description: Sentence Completion Questions will be dealt with in this video. Although sentence completion questions are one of the less prevalent types of IELTS Listening questions, you should be prepared to answer them if you are given one. They are a form of gap fill question in which you must listen to the tape and complete the phrases with the missing words.

details.title: Labeling Maps/Plan
details.description: Maps and plans test your ability to visualize a 3D space with the help of an audio. It is typically a monologue and tour guidance is the commonly chosen theme. Learn how to tackle the question of maps in this video.

details.title: Diagram Labeling

details.title: Matching Questions
details.description:
Matching questions are particularly common in Section 1, where you must listen for detail in a two-person conversation.
You'll have to match objects from two different lists of alternatives. You must, for example, match the hotels (A–E) with the descriptions (1–4).

details.title: Multiple Choice-questions
details.description: In multiple choice questions, you are required to choose the correct answer from a shortlist (usually 3 words or phrases). Often the answers will look similar in meaning so you will need to listen very carefully. Don’t just select the first answer you hear. For more details, have a look at our video.
